From ae1ecd321d9eae0bd2da9851645d882659ca6809 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dan on Selwyn <dan@awto.au>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 16:16:22 +1000
Subject: [PATCH] lib: translate decompress to Rust (linux-rs TU 22)

Magic-number decompressor dispatch table. Every CONFIG_DECOMPRESS_*
option is unset in our target config, so every table entry's
decompressor slot is a NULL fn pointer here, exactly as in the C
(#define gunzip NULL etc.) -- not dead code to skip, the table
structure and magic-number matching (first two bytes of input) are
live and exercised; only the individual decompressor symbols are
absent for this config.

__init/__initconst (freed after boot) expressed via #[link_section]
matching the sections vmlinux.lds.h reserves for them -- verified via
readelf that both .init.text and .init.rodata actually landed in the
compiled object, not just asserted.

New shim: rust_helper_pr_debug_decompress_magic (rust/helpers/print.c).
kernel::print's pr_debug! needs a crate-root __LOG_PREFIX normally set
by module!{}, which a per-file lib/*_rs.rs translation has no access to
-- shimmed the exact C macro call instead (rule 0014 extended; C
varargs macros can't be wrapped generically across FFI regardless, so
one shim per format string is the right granularity, same as the llist
per-operand shims).

Validated: builds, boots, all suites green; decompress_method confirmed
in System.map, section placement confirmed via readelf.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 lib/Makefile                    |   9 ++-
 lib/decompress_rs.rs            | 104 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 rust/bindings/bindings_helper.h |   1 +
 rust/helpers/helpers.c          |   1 +
 rust/helpers/print.c            |  21 +++++++
 5 files changed, 135 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)
 create mode 100644 lib/decompress_rs.rs
 create mode 100644 rust/helpers/print.c

